nessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-online-financial-advisors%5C%22%3Efinancial%20advisors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20self-made%20millionaires%20all%20preaching%20the%20same%20thing%3A%20invest%20for%20the%20long-term%3B%20don't%20try%20to%20time%20the%20market%3B%20and%20let%20your%20investments%20compound%20over%20many%20years.%20Most%20of%20us%20would%20rather%20cover%20our%20ears%20and%20hope%20to%20get%20rich%20quick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20spoke%20with%20Rachel%20Wooten%2C%20a%20CPA%20and%20then-finance%20director%20at%20the%20Flint%20Group%2C%20she%20confirmed%20that%20there's%20plenty%20of%20money%20advice%20no%20one%20wants%20to%20hear%2C%20but%20everyone%20should%20follow.%20Here%20are%20four%20things%20she%20wants%20you%20to%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20Invest%20the%20maximum%20possible%20in%20your%20health%20savings%20account%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-much-do-i-need-to-retire%5C%22%3Eretirement%20planning%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20most%20of%20us%20have%20heard%20that%20we%20should%20max%20out%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-ira-accounts%5C%22%3EIRA%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%3E401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20a%20just-as-helpful%20retirement%20tool%20that%20you%20should%20also%20max%20out%20is%20your%20health%20savings%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20HSA%20is%20a%20tax-advantaged%20savings%20account%20created%20in%202003%20to%20help%20people%20with%20high-deductible%20health%20plans%20pay%20for%20out-of-pocket%20medical%20expenses.%20Although%20the%20purpose%20of%20an%20HSA%20is%20to%20save%20money%20for%20inevitable%20healthcare%20expenses%2C%20you%20can%20just%20as%20easily%20use%20your%20HSA%20as%20an%20investing%20tool.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20HSA%20is%20the%20only%20account%20that%20allows%20you%20to%20pay%20no%20taxes%20at%20all%20on%20contributions%2C%20growth%2C%20or%20withdrawals%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Wooten.%20%26quot%3BInvest%20your%20HSA%20funds%20and%20avoid%20reimbursing%20yourself%20for%20those%20expensive%20braces%20or%20doctor%20visits%2C%20and%20you'll%20come%20out%20ahead%20in%20the%20long%20run.%26quot%3B%20Also%2C%20if%20you%20leave%20your%20HSA%20money%20in%20your%20account%20until%20age%2065%2C%20you%20can%20withdraw%20your%20HSA%20funds%20for%20non-medical%20expenses%20at%20any%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20Put%20your%20investments%20on%20auto-pilot%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20juggling%20work%2C%20family%2C%20and%20hobbies%2C%20the%20last%20thing%20most%20of%20us%20want%20to%20think%20about%20is%20actively%20trading%20a%20portfolio.%20That's%20why%20one%20of%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20set%20yourself%20up%20for%20the%20future%20is%20through%20an%20employer-sponsored%20retirement%20plan.%20These%20are%20attractive%2C%20passive%20options%20that%20most%20employees%20can%20take%20advantage%20of.%20All%20you%20have%20to%20do%20is%20select%20how%20much%20of%20your%20paycheck%20you%20want%20to%20contribute%20each%20pay%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20strategy%20is%20to%20put%20your%20investments%20in%20a%20total%20market%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fhow-to-invest-in-index-funds%5C%22%3Eindex%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-an-etf%5C%22%3Eexchange-traded%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20then%20forget%20them.%20%26quot%3BSure%2C%20trading%20stocks%20is%20fun%20and%20a%20lot%20more%20interesting%20than%20this%20boring%20strategy%2C%20but%20over%20the%20long%20term%2C%20you%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20lose%20money%20actively%20trading%20than%20to%20beat%20market%20returns%2C%26quot%3B%20Wooten%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Avoid%20lifestyle%20creep%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20what%20you%20make.%20It's%20what%20you%20keep.%20Unfortunately%2C%20this%20idea%20gets%20lost%20on%20most%20people%20after%20they%20get%20a%20raise.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20a%20salary%20increase%2C%20many%20people%20immediately%20consider%20upgrading%20their%20house%20or%20vehicle.%20However%2C%20studies%20have%20shown%20that%20cars%2C%20houses%2C%20etc.%2C%20can%20become%20quickly%20acclimated%20to%2C%20so%20the%20uplift%20in%20happiness%20is%20short-lived%2C%26quot%3B%20Wooten%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20can%20avoid%20this%20tendency%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Flifestyle-creep%5C%22%3Elifestyle%20creep%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20instead%20boost%20your%20savings%20and%20investments%20when%20you%20get%20a%20raise%20or%20bonus%2C%20you%20can%20significantly%20decrease%20your%20financial%20stress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20there%20are%20exceptions%20to%20this%20rule%2C%20as%20maybe%20there%20is%20a%20house%20repair%20or%20medical%20emergency%20you%20have%20been%20putting%20off%20for%20financial%20reasons.%20However%2C%20to%20become%20financially%20secure%2C%20consider%20upgrades%20carefully%20before%20committing%20to%20a%20higher%20standard%20of%20living.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Start%20saving%20for%20retirement%20as%20early%20as%20possible%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20most%20people%20just%20starting%20their%20careers%2C%20it's%20difficult%20to%20set%20money%20aside%20for%20something%20as%20far%20down%20the%20road%20as%20retirement.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20convince%20a%20person%20in%20their%2020s%20to%20consider%20the%20well-being%20of%20their%20older%20self%2C%20but%20money%20stashed%20away%20early%20in%20your%20career%20will%20have%20the%20benefit%20of%20compounding%20doing%20the%20heavy%20lifting%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Wooten.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20see%20the%20importance%20of%20investing%20earlier%20rather%20than%20later%2C%20let's%20look%20at%20this%20example%20(you%20can%20run%20your%20own%20through%20our%20free%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fretirement-calculator%5C%22%3Eretirement%20calculator%3C%2Fa%3E).%20Two%20people%20save%20%24100%20a%20month%20for%20retirement%2C%20each%20has%20a%205%25%20annual%20compound%20rate%20of%20return%2C%20but%20one%20starts%20at%2025%2C%20and%20the%20other%20starts%20at%2035.%20The%20one%20who%20started%20at%2025%20will%20have%20saved%20nearly%20twice%20as%20much%20by%20age%2065.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20person%20who%20started%20investing%20at%2025%20will%20have%20roughly%20%24162%2C000%20in%20their%20account%2C%20while%20the%20person%20who%20started%20at%2035%20will%20only%20have%20%2489%2C000.%20This%20is%20the%20power%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-compound-interest%5C%22%3Ecompound%20interest%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%2025-year-old%20investor%20would%20have%20only%20invested%20%2412%2C000%20more%20of%20their%20own%20money%2C%20yet%20they%20would%20have%20over%20%2470%2C000%20more%20than%20the%20person%20who%20started%20at%2035.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinding%20a%20financial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20hard.%20SmartAsset's%20free%20tool%20matches%20you%20with%20up%20to%20three%20fiduciary%20financial%20advisors%20that%20serve%20your%20area%20in%20minutes.%20Each%20advisor%20has%20been%20vetted%20by%20SmartAsset%20and%20is%20held%20to%20a%20fiduciary%20standard%20to%20act%20in%20your%20best%20interests.%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsmartasset.com%2Fretirement%2Ffind-a-financial-planner%3Futm_source%3Dbusinessinsider%26utm_medium%3Dcpc%26utm_campaign%3Dbus__falc_bicontent%26utm_content%3DBI%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Start%20your%20search%20now.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C