g%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20story%20is%20part%20of%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fwhats-next-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20Next%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20series%20about%20business%20leaders'%20strategies%20for%20workplace%20productivity.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Josh%20Campo%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20ad%20agency%20Razorfish.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20a%20services%20business%2C%20so%20obviously%20we%20work%20on%20number%20of%20%5Bbillable%5D%20hours.%20But%20that's%20not%20a%20very%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Febay-ceo-jamie-iannone-produtivity-efficiency-ai-change-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Euseful%20metric%20for%20productivity%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20look%20at%20how%20we're%20driving%20success%20and%20the%20relevance%20of%20the%20ideas%20that%20we%20come%20up%20with.%20We're%20essentially%20an%20idea%20company%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0we%20come%20up%20with%20plans%20to%20solve%20a%20client's%20business%20challenge.%20The%20relevance%20of%20those%20ideas%20really%20dictate%3A%20Are%20we%20growing%20and%20winning%20more%20clients%20and%20doing%20more%20work%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20we've%20expanded%20to%20almost%202%2C000%20people%2C%20the%20challenge%20has%20been%20to%20figure%20out%20ways%20to%20maintain%20the%20values%20and%20culture%20that%20got%20us%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20mandated%20that%20people%20come%20back%20to%20the%20office%20three%20days%20a%20week%2C%20but%20we%20have%20always%20been%20pretty%20invested%20in%20providing%20flexibility.%20Teams%20and%20Zoom%20are%20great%2C%20but%20there's%20a%20certain%20magic%20when%20you're%20in%20the%20room%20together%20trying%20to%20hash%20out%20a%20challenge%20and%20figure%20out%20the%20right%20solution%20for%20a%20client.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20there%20was%20a%20policy%2C%20people%20were%20starting%20to%20come%20back%20in%2C%20but%20you%20could%20show%20up%20on%20a%20day%20and%20maybe%20see%20three%20people.%20As%20much%20as%20it%20would%20be%20great%20for%20everyone%20to%20be%20self-organized%2C%20when%20Publicis%20is%20almost%2090%2C000%20people%2C%20and%20Razorfish%20is%20almost%202%2C000%2C%20you%20do%20create%20a%20sense%20of%20disappointment%20when%20folks%20come%20in%20and%20they're%20one%20of%2010%20people%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20one%20of%20100.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-mandates-remote-work-stock-returns-productivity-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eskepticism%20around%20that%20approach%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20does%20provide%20for%20a%20better%20experience%20overall%20knowing%20people%20will%20be%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20earlier%20COVID%20days%2C%20when%20we%20were%20all%20remote%2C%20we%20found%20ways%20to%20connect%20with%20folks%20and%20instill%20the%20values%20of%20the%20organization.%20As%20we%20came%20back%20to%20the%20office%2C%20the%20muscle%20memory%20of%20what%20we%20had%20done%20for%20years%20and%20years%20was%20not%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFrom%20listening%20tours%20to%20Taco%20Tuesdays%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20to%20come%20up%20with%20new%20rituals%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fusing-apple-vision-pro-for-the-day-productivity-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecreate%20consistency%3C%2Fa%3E%20among%20team%20members.%20That%20was%20probably%20one%20of%20the%20most%20significant%20challenges%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20before%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-mandates-remote-work-stock-returns-productivity-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn-to-office%20mandate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%202023%2C%20we%20started%20office%20tours.%20Our%20president%20and%20I%20did%20a%20%26quot%3B10%20cities%20in%2010%20days%26quot%3B%20tour%20and%20just%20went%20to%20go%20talk%20to%20people%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20this%20is%20what%20the%20year%20is%20going%20to%20be%20about.%26quot%3B%20We%20had%20other%20leaders%20go%20and%20do%20listening%20tours.%20We%20also%20had%20remote%20sessions%20for%20everything%2C%20so%20everything%20is%20done%20in%20parity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20thing%20we%20do%20is%20monthly%20Q%26amp%3BAs%20we%20call%20%26quot%3BOpen%20Doors%26quot%3B%20where%20anybody%20can%20ask%20me%20and%20other%20leaders%20any%20question%20they%20want.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20rituals%20we%20started%20were%20quarterly%20monetary%20awards%20that%20recognize%20the%20values%20of%20the%20organization%3A%20accountable%2C%20entrepreneurial%2C%20progressive%2C%20passionate%2C%20and%20kind.%20And%20%26quot%3BRazorfish%20Week%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20focused%20on%20celebrating%20aspects%20of%20the%20in-office%20experience%2C%20with%20things%20like%20a%20service%20day%20and%20leaders%20talking%20about%20their%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20brought%20back%20pre-COVID%20rituals%20like%20Bagel%20Wednesday%20and%20Taco%20Tuesday.%20Food%20is%20a%20big%20part%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheres-how-reengage-employees-checked-out-work-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20engagement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20creating%20those%20bonding%20moments%20for%20folks%20and%20reminding%20them%20of%20some%20of%20the%20upsides%20of%20being%20in%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20city-rollout%20tours%20are%20pretty%20popular%20in%20terms%20of%20how%20well%20they're%20attended.%20I'd%20say%20we're%20probably%20at%20about%2080%25%20of%20folks%20in%20any%20given%20location.%20The%20Open%20Doors%20sessions%20can%20be%20quite%20well%20attended.%20I%20think%20they%20resonate%20because%20of%20their%20transparency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20ask%20a%20lot%20of%20our%20people%20in%20terms%20of%20working%20hard%20and%20delivering%20for%20our%20clients.%20We%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-transparent-leadership-is-critical-during-times-of-crisis-2021-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eowe%20them%20transparency%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20basically%20anything%20that%20we%20can%20tell%20them%20about%2C%20whether%20it's%20the%20business%2C%20whether%20it's%20about%20clients%2C%20whether%20it's%20about%20policies.%20I%20do%20think%20that%20that%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20appreciated%20aspects%20of%20our%20people%20and%20working%20at%20Razorfish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20do%20get%20tough%20questions%20sometimes.%20Some%20days%20I%20feel%20like%20we've%20got%20a%20couple%20hundred%20people%2C%20and%20other%20days%20there's%20almost%201%2C000.%20I'm%20always%20wondering%20when%20I%20join%20and%20there%20are%201%2C000%20people%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20what%20is%20somebody%20going%20to%20ask%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20having%20success%20in%20terms%20of%20winning%20new%20clients%20and%20expanding%20our%20relationships%20with%20existing%20clients.%20And%20that%2C%20to%20me%2C%20is%20ultimately%20the%20best%20metric%20of%20productivity.%20Another%20area%20that%20I%20would%20look%20at%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhere-are-reasons-employees-stay-beyond-the-salary-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etalent-retention%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20have%20been%20better%20than%20the%20industry%20average%2C%20even%20through%20very%20highly%20competitive%20periods%20of%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years.%20We%20do%20engagement%20surveys%2C%20which%2C%20by%20and%20large%2C%20come%20back%20favorable%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%2