iculture%20Ministry%20looking%20for%20ideas%20revolving%20around%20additional%20livelihoods%20in%20agriculture.%20Sawant%20seized%20the%20opportunity%20and%20pitched%20rural%20tourism%20as%20a%20potential%20idea.%20%E2%80%9CToday%20the%20villages%20of%20India%20are%20empty.%20People%20are%20moving%20away.%20Village%20tourism%20will%20not%20only%20help%20generate%20employment%20for%20the%20locals%20but%20give%20them%20a%20reason%20to%20stay%20back%20in%20the%20villages.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESawant%20also%20started%20a%20textile%20upscaling%20project%20in%20the%20state%20wherein%20she%20encouraged%2060%20women%20to%20earn%20through%20patchwork%20items%20such%20as%20quilts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20fascinating%20is%20that%20Sawant%E2%80%99s%20slew%20of%20projects%20are%20not%20only%20focused%20on%20empowering%20women%20but%20doing%20this%20while%20helping%20city%20folk%20have%20an%20unparalleled%20holiday%20experience.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20rural%20tourism%20project%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh.%20She%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20village%20called%20%E2%80%98Veerapuram%E2%80%99%20was%20given%20to%20us%20to%20develop.%20The%20village%20is%20a%20hotspot%20for%20the%20migratory%20birds%20that%20come%20to%20nest%20here%20from%20August%20to%20January%20every%20year.%20Over%20thousands%20of%20these%20birds%20flock%20here.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESawant%20organised%2020%20women%20into%20self-help%20groups%20that%20would%20conduct%20and%20benefit%20from%20bird%20tourism.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20women%20were%20trained%20to%20take%20the%20tourists%20around%20the%20village%2C%20explain%20to%20them%20about%20these%20birds%20and%20their%20migration%20patterns%20and%20show%20them%20their%20nests.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Sawant%20looks%20back%20on%20how%20she%20has%20succeeded%20in%20bridging%20the%20gap%20between%20tourists%20looking%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F308710%2Ftentgram-provides-experiential-travel-across-india-wayanad-kashmir-meghalaya-himachal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexperiential%20travel%20%3C%2Fa%3Eon%20one%20side%20and%20villagers%20looking%20to%20earn%20on%20the%20other%2C%20she%20smiles%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20a%20vision%20to%20help%205%2C000%20women%20in%20the%20next%20few%20years.%20Because%20every%20woman%20empowered%20is%20a%20family%20empowered.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Padmashree%20Pande%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711353859000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fwomen-empowerment--1710768304.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D345085%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rashmi%20Sawant%20is%20the%20founder%20of%20'Culture%20Aangan'%2C%20an%20experiential%20travel%20platform%20that%20aims%20to%20promote%20sustainable%20rural%20tourism%20and%20support%20grass%20root%20development%20projects%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Uttarakhand%20and%20Sindhudurg%20district%20of%20Maharashtra.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Krystelle%20Dsouza%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A45%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F345085%2Feco-tourism-helps-rural-woman-earn-mangroves-of-sindhudurg-rashmi-sawant-homestays-konkan%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Startup%E2%80%99s%20Innovation%20Could%20Help%20Millions%20Get%20Access%20to%20Better%20Brain%20Health%20At%20Home%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIsaac%20John%E2%80%99s%20father%20was%20first%20diagnosed%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F329667%2Fpalghar-kiran-kamdar-free-homemade-khichdi-for-patients-hospital-parkinson-disease%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EParkinson%E2%80%99s%20disease%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202016.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20Issac%20was%20on%20a%20brief%20sabbatical%20from%20his%20corporate%20life%20in%20Bengaluru%20while%20his%20father%20was%20working%20in%20Vapi%2C%20Gujarat.%20Witnessing%20his%20father%20struggle%20with%20this%20neurodegenerative%20condition%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%C2%A0%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20Issac%20recalls%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20began%20with%20involuntary%20shaking%20of%20his%20hands%20without%20anyone%20taking%20note%20of%20it.%20We%20waited%20for%20months%20before%20seeking%20medical%20input.%20He%20was%20put%20on%20a%20medicine%20called%20Syndopa%20that%20continued%20throughout%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20life%20along%20with%20certain%20vitamin%20supplements.%20While%20he%20worked%20for%20another%20year%20after%20his%20first%20diagnosis%2C%20driving%20a%20car%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20things%20he%20had%20to%20give%20up%2C%20and%20subsequently%2C%20his%20job%20as%20well.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20some%20time%2C%20Issac%E2%80%99s%20father%20was%20compelled%20to%20move%20to%20a%20small%20town%20in%20Kerala%20and%20live%20with%20their%20joint%20family.%20Since%20then%2C%20they%20had%20to%20engage%20in%20%E2%80%98steady%20management%E2%80%99%20of%20his%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20received%20little%20guidance%20on%20what%20diet%20or%20lifestyle%20would%20help%20him%20cope%20better.%20Living%20in%20a%20small%20town%20in%20Kerala%2C%20access%20to%20high-quality%20neurological%20experts%20was%20also%20limited.%20Our%20family%20and%20I%20accepted%20the%20status%20quo%20and%20slowly%20he%20withdrew%20from%20other%20social%20activities.%20He%20wanted%20to%20resume%20work%20in%20some%20way%2C%20but%20the%20shaking%20of%20the%20hands%20transferred%20to%20the%20legs%20as%20well%20in%20a%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20and%20he%20had%20to%20have%20someone%20around%20for%20mobility%20around%20the%20house%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20a%20point%2C%20the%20medication%20did%20little%20to%20improve%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20quality%20of%20life%3B%20seeing%20it%20deteriorate%20like%20that%20despite%20the%20medication%20had%20a%20profound%20impact%20on%20Isaac.%20Tragically%2C%20he%20passed%20away%20in%202020%20amid%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Rahul%20Krishnan%2C%20who%20comes%20from%20a%20large%20joint%20family%20in%20Ernakulam%2C%20Kerala%2C%20also%20witnessed%20firsthand%20the%20struggles%20of%20loneliness%20and%20isolation%20among%20his%20older%20relatives%2C%20particularly%20those%20dealing%20with%20neurodegenerative%20conditions.%20With%20the%20added%20strain%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20there%20was%20news%20every%20day%20of%20someone%E2%80%99s%20cognitive%20health%20in%20the%20family%20deteriorating.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%C2%A0%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20Rahul%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20come%20from%20a%20large%20joint%20family%20in%20Kerala.%20Like%20me%2C%20many%20of%20my%20cousins%20and%20friends%20ventured%20away%20from%20home%20in%20pursuit%20of%20better%20educational%20and%20career%20prospects.%20With%20the%20rise%20of%20nuclear%20families%2C%20meeting%20elders%20became%20a%20yearly%20affair%20at%20best.%20But%20witnessing%20the%20rapid%20ageing%20and%20forgetfulness%20of%20our%20loved%20ones%20has%20always%20made%20me%20wonder%20why%20there%20are%20no%20tools%20for%20early%20detection%20of%20memory%20decline.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20I%20encouraged%20my%20father%20to%20play%20sudoku%20and%20solve%20puzzle%20books%20to%20keep%20his%20mind%20sharp%20and%20active%2C%20I%20recognised%20a%20latent%20concern%20in%20almost%20every%20family%20like%20mine.%20The%20realisation%20that%20there%20is%20a%20significant%20gap%20in%20awareness%20and%20access%20to%20resources%20aimed%20at%20understanding%20and%20arresting%20cognitive%20decline%20served%20as%20a%20key%20driving%20force%20behind%20the%20inception%20of%20%E2%80%98Ivory%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20meeting%20each%20other%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20July%202022%20during%20a%20residency%20programme%20for%20aspiring%20entrepreneurs%20run%20by%20Antler%2C%20an%20early-stage%20venture%20capitalist%20(VC)%20firm%2C%20Issac%20and%20Rahul%20would%20come%20together%20to%20establish%20%E2%80%98Ivory%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFounded%20in%20October%202022%2C%20this%20Mumbai-based%20%E2%80%98age-tech%E2%80%99%20startup%20is%20working%20towards%20redefining%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20ageing%20experience%E2%80%9D%20by%20focusing%20on%20%E2%80%9Cbetter%20brain%20health%20through%20neuroscience-backed%20assessments%2C%20interactive%20games%2C%20and%20personalised%20solutions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FIssac-John-and-Rahul-Krishnan-Founder-1711111144.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Co-founders%20of%20Ivory%3A%20Issac%20John%20and%20Rahul%20Krishnan%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FIssac-John-and-Rahul-Krishnan-Founder-1711111144.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FIssac-John-and-Rahul-Krishnan-Founder-1711111144-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FIssac-John-and-Rahul-Krishnan-Founder-1711111144-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FIssac-John-and-Rahul-Krishnan-Founder-1711111144-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FIssac-John-and-Rahul-Krishnan-Founder-1711111144-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-345585%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ECo-founders%20of%20Ivory%3A%20Issac%20John%20and%20Rahul%20Krishnan%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C